In a speech at the Organization of American States, Vice President Mike Pence addressed the Western Hemisphere's commitment to security, prosperity, and freedom. He emphasized that the United States will always prioritize the security and prosperity of America, but it does not mean America alone. Pence highlighted the importance of economic cooperation and trade relationships in the region, as well as the need for strong security partnerships to combat crime and corruption. He specifically called out the crises in Nicaragua and Venezuela, urging the international community to take concrete actions to hold their leaders accountable and support the people of those countries. Pence also called for the suspension of Venezuela from the Organization of American States and emphasized the importance of upholding democracy and freedom in the region.